The paper deals with fingerprint recognition systems, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The evaluation of the individual sub-components of the system falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the study of minutiae-based matchers is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
